        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <para>3900FC bus chassis built from February 15, 1991, through September 16, 1993, and 3000FE bus
                    chassis built from January 1, 1994, through September 13, 1994, were manufactured with standard duty
                    front shock absorbers. This, along with the parabolic front springs provide a soft ride, which under
                    certain road conditions may be perceived by some customers as being too soft. For customers who want
                    to stiffen the ride on the front of their vehicles, the standard duty front shock absorbers may be
                    replaced with heavy duty front shock absorbers.
                </para>
                <para>This letter contains parts and service information to replace the standard duty front shock
                    absorbers with heavy duty front shock absorbers on the above listed vehicles.
                </para>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
