        <svcproc svcproctype="replace" graphiccount="1">
            <title>SERVICE PROCEDURE</title>
            <para>Refer to the Parts List for all item numbers listed below.</para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the shock absorber. Save lower mounting hardware for installation of the new
                    shock absorber.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Locate and drill two 21/32 inch holes in the frame rails for the new upper shock
                    bracket, right and left sides as illustrated in
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9403031">Figure 1</hotlnk>. Measure forward 17-3/16 inches from the front of the
                    rear spring mount for the vertical location of the two holes (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9403031">Figure 1</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f9403031" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G9403031.webp" type="webp" resolution="300"/>
                    <caption>Figure 1.</caption>
                </figure>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>3000FE bus chassis built from January 1, 1994, through September 13, 1994, have holes
                            already drilled in the frame to accept the upper shock absorber bracket.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position the upper shock bracket (Item 1) in place and install the two hex flanged head
                    bolts (Item 2) and flanged hex self-locking nuts (Item 3) as illustrated in
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9403031">Figure 1</hotlnk>. Tighten to 200-240 ft-lbs. (271-325 N&#8226;m).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place the washer (Item 4), bushing (Item 5) and shock absorber mounting spacer (Item 6)
                    over the upper threaded turret end of the new shock absorber (Item 8). Position the upper turret end
                    through the upper shock bracket and install another bushing (Item 5), washer (Item 4) and &#x215D;-18
                    UNF hex self-locking nut (Item 7). Do not tighten.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position the lower end of the new shock absorber in place and install the &#190;-10 UNC
                    X 8 inch hex bolt, shock absorber mounting washers, spacer and hex self-locking nut removed with the
                    old shock absorber. Tighten to 175-215 ft-lbs. (237-291 N&#8226;m).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tighten the shock absorber upper mounting &#x215D;-18 hex self-locking nut to 105-125
                    ft-lbs. (142-170 N&#8226;m).
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
